01:00:37,601 --> 01:00:41,571
because that's the only way
he could reach
the final completion

986
01:00:41,706 --> 01:00:43,607
of being the hero
in his own story.

987
01:00:43,741 --> 01:00:47,244
It was not enough to have
an A-list actor.
It had to be him.

988
01:00:47,377 --> 01:00:49,914
The acting that Barry did
in the film,

989
01:00:50,047 --> 01:00:52,216
was, I thought,
very, very, very good.

990
01:00:52,349 --> 01:00:55,252
I know when he wanted to
make this movie...

991
01:00:55,385 --> 01:00:57,888
There again, I said,
"Barry, be very,
very careful."

992
01:00:58,022 --> 01:01:00,257
I certainly advised him
not to play himself.

993
01:01:00,390 --> 01:01:02,592
I said,
"You're making a mistake."

994
01:01:02,727 --> 01:01:05,963
Sorry. Hold on. There you go.

995
01:01:08,866 --> 01:01:10,634
There we go.

996
01:01:12,236 --> 01:01:14,138
Mind if I smoke?

997
01:01:14,271 --> 01:01:15,472
No, go ahead.

998
01:01:15,605 --> 01:01:17,541
I don't smoke.
I mean, not anymore.

999
01:01:17,674 --> 01:01:20,845
I was just curious
what a preacher felt
about that.

1000
01:01:20,978 --> 01:01:23,881
But now, unfortunately,
I'm hooked on these.

1001
01:01:24,014 --> 01:01:28,552
I got to go to rehab
for these. Want one?

1002
01:01:28,685 --> 01:01:31,121
No.
It's the red one.

1003
01:01:31,255 --> 01:01:32,556
Go ahead. No.

1004
01:01:34,491 --> 01:01:35,726
What are you thinking about?

1005
01:01:36,761 --> 01:01:37,728
Nah.

1006
01:01:39,696 --> 01:01:40,765
Peanut.

1007
01:01:40,898 --> 01:01:41,999
What's that?

1008
01:01:42,132 --> 01:01:43,901
James "Peanut" Long.

1009
01:01:44,034 --> 01:01:46,670
The reason they call me
the Jailhouse Preacher.

1010
01:01:46,804 --> 01:01:51,208
Oh. You're gonna tell me
how you found Jesus?

1011
01:01:51,341 --> 01:01:53,277
I didn't find Jesus.

1012
01:01:53,410 --> 01:01:57,581
He found me in the form of
a 250-pound black guy.

1013
01:02:00,184 --> 01:02:01,451
* Yeah

1014
01:02:04,855 --> 01:02:06,390
* uh-huh

1015
01:02:08,058 --> 01:02:12,462
* It's a matter of life
or a matter after of death *

1016
01:02:12,596 --> 01:02:14,631
Not bad for a guy your size.

1017
01:02:15,599 --> 01:02:17,467
Size ain't nothing.

1018
01:02:18,502 --> 01:02:20,337
The body is your temple.

1019
01:02:21,605 --> 01:02:25,976
Muscles ain't strength.

1020
01:02:31,515 --> 01:02:33,517
Real strength is in here.

1021
01:02:35,619 --> 01:02:40,290
You know,
the most dangerous part
of your story

1022
01:02:40,424 --> 01:02:42,226
is that throughout
the whole ordeal

1023
01:02:42,359 --> 01:02:43,760
you actually
convinced yourself

1024
01:02:43,894 --> 01:02:46,630
that you were helping
hundreds of employees,

1025
01:02:46,763 --> 01:02:48,332
when in reality,
you were just...

1026
01:02:48,465 --> 01:02:51,035
Helping myself.
That's all I was doing.

1027
01:02:51,168 --> 01:02:55,139
Hindsight is 20/20,
and look where it got me.

1028
01:02:55,272 --> 01:02:57,541
Locked up in a prison cell.

1029
01:02:58,608 --> 01:03:00,978
Well, we're both locked up.

1030
01:03:01,111 --> 01:03:04,281
Difference is,
I'm at peace with
what I've done.

1031
01:03:04,414 --> 01:03:05,715
And I'm getting there.

1032
01:03:05,850 --> 01:03:07,717
You're pretending
to get there.

1033
01:03:10,187 --> 01:03:11,355
You don't think I'm sincere?

1034
01:03:11,488 --> 01:03:13,790
I think you're trying
to find the Lord,

1035
01:03:13,924 --> 01:03:15,592
so you can hang out
with the Jesus freaks

1036
01:03:15,725 --> 01:03:19,129
instead of the skinheads
to make it in here.

1037
01:03:19,263 --> 01:03:21,465
Whatever.
Yeah. Whatever.

1038
01:03:21,598 --> 01:03:24,835
Why do you come to church
on Sunday

1039
01:03:24,969 --> 01:03:29,239
Is it because you're really
trying to change your life?

1040
01:03:29,373 --> 01:03:31,641
Or is it just another
Barry Minkow con?

1041
01:03:31,775 --> 01:03:35,645
* What if I told you...
A second chance to live *

1042
01:03:35,779 --> 01:03:37,747
One thing to remember
is the fraud artist

1043
01:03:37,882 --> 01:03:40,050
doesn't see himself
as a criminal.

1044
01:03:40,184 --> 01:03:44,021
The fraud is merely a means
to a well-justified end.

1045
01:03:44,154 --> 01:03:47,057
Once the scheme works,
everybody gets paid off,

1046
01:03:47,191 --> 01:03:48,725
nobody gets hurt.

1047
01:03:49,459 --> 01:03:50,794
Voila.

1048
01:03:51,628 --> 01:03:54,464
Okay, let's move on here.

1049
01:03:56,934 --> 01:04:01,238
You know as well as I do,
when the devil comes at you
at first,

1050
01:04:01,371 --> 01:04:05,242
he looks good, sounds good,
feels good.

1051
01:04:05,375 --> 01:04:09,546
Then, when it's too late,
the beast comes out.

1052
01:04:09,679 --> 01:04:11,515
You got that right.

1053
01:04:13,183 --> 01:04:14,751
Where were you 11 years ago?

1054
01:04:15,785 --> 01:04:18,655
Well, I had a lot of
growing up to do.

1055
01:04:18,788 --> 01:04:23,093
Like I said,
ain't no accidents in life.

1056
01:04:23,227 --> 01:04:25,829
We bought shares
for five cents apiece,

1057
01:04:25,963 --> 01:04:27,464
then dumped them on the market

1058
01:04:27,597 --> 01:04:29,866
when it hit 12 and 13 bucks.

1059
01:04:30,000 --> 01:04:32,502
That was the part
that was illegal.

1060
01:04:32,636 --> 01:04:35,772
So, it was Saxon
that got you involved
in the penny stocks, right?

1061
01:04:35,906 --> 01:04:38,142
And that's when he turned
his Wall Street connections

1062
01:04:38,275 --> 01:04:40,777
onto the stock,
they bought blocks of it,

1063
01:04:40,911 --> 01:04:42,712
the price shot through
the roof

1064
01:04:42,846 --> 01:04:46,250
and I was worth
millions instantly.

1065
01:04:46,383 --> 01:04:47,851
Insider trading.

1066
01:04:56,526 --> 01:04:57,861
Hey!

1067
01:04:58,428 --> 01:04:59,663
Hey!

1068
01:05:01,065 --> 01:05:03,800
Hey, you need to
leave him alone.

1069
01:05:03,934 --> 01:05:05,902
Yeah? You need to
mind your own business.

1070
01:05:06,036 --> 01:05:07,571
Hey, I don't want any trouble.

1071
01:05:08,672 --> 01:05:10,807
I said
mind your own business.

1072
01:05:10,941 --> 01:05:13,543
I will when you let him go.

1073
01:05:13,677 --> 01:05:15,345
Too bad.
Can't you hear?

1074
01:05:15,479 --> 01:05:17,547
Finish your shower.
I said take a walk, man.
Take a walk.

1075
01:05:17,681 --> 01:05:19,950
I don't think so.
Don't think so?

1076
01:05:22,386 --> 01:05:27,057
I know I'm not seeing
what I think I'm seeing.

1077
01:05:30,327 --> 01:05:36,266
'Cause if you're trying
to hurt him,
you're trying to hurt me.

1078
01:05:36,400 --> 01:05:37,701
Let's get out of here.

1079
01:05:43,573 --> 01:05:45,909
Lord Jesus,
I want to thank you

1080
01:05:46,043 --> 01:05:48,878
for making me
a God-fearing man.

1081
01:05:49,013 --> 01:05:51,648
And having me
not beat anyone's ass.

1082
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:54,851
In Jesus' name, Amen.

1083
01:06:01,725 --> 01:06:03,593
I'm proud of you, whiz kid.

1084
01:06:04,461 --> 01:06:05,795
You did all the work.

1085
01:06:05,929 --> 01:06:08,332
I don't know why
you'd be proud of me.

1086
01:06:08,465 --> 01:06:10,067
Changing.

1087
01:06:10,200 --> 01:06:14,304
You helped a weaker brother
who was outnumbered.

1088
01:06:14,438 --> 01:06:19,409
Shows that you're changing
from your selfish-ass,
self-centered ways.

1089
01:06:19,543 --> 01:06:23,780
Remember. The Lord always
looks out for the underdog.

1090
01:06:25,782 --> 01:06:29,286
BARRY: I don't know
if it was Peanut
or the broken nose.

1091
01:06:29,419 --> 01:06:33,057
I guess God has a way
of taking care of the details.

1092
01:06:33,190 --> 01:06:39,896
And it was at this moment
that life took on new clarity
for me.

1093
01:06:40,030 --> 01:06:42,699
See, to win the game,
I had to stay in the pocket,

1094
01:06:42,832 --> 01:06:45,001
and face the pain.

1095
01:06:45,135 --> 01:06:48,705
It was then I learned
that to win in life

1096
01:06:48,838 --> 01:06:51,741
meant no more backing down.

1097
01:06:53,009 --> 01:06:54,711
No more shortcuts.

1098
01:06:55,712 --> 01:06:57,847
No more compromises.

1099
01:06:58,848 --> 01:07:00,384
No more lies.

1100
01:07:04,254 --> 01:07:05,889
And no more cons.

1101
01:07:36,453 --> 01:07:38,488
How you feeling?

1102
01:07:38,622 --> 01:07:42,426
DAN: I question whether
some of the stuff he did
was for the movie

1103
01:07:42,559 --> 01:07:44,060
or the story of the movie.

1104
01:07:44,194 --> 01:07:46,496
I never felt better.
Thank you.

1105
01:07:46,630 --> 01:07:49,299
DAN: I question whether
Peanut was a real person
or not.

1106
01:07:49,433 --> 01:07:51,401
It's a pretty good throw.

1107
01:07:51,535 --> 01:07:54,771
MIKEY: I don't think
Barry could throw
a football nine feet.

1108
01:07:54,904 --> 01:07:57,141
Truth plus time equal trust.

1109
01:07:57,274 --> 01:08:01,945
A lot of truth, over a long
period of time equals trust.

1110
01:08:02,078 --> 01:08:04,948
And no shortcuts
to that equation either,
you know?

1111
01:08:14,858 --> 01:08:19,329
Yeah, well,
thanks for the time.

1112
01:08:24,268 --> 01:08:26,536
BARRY: Like I said
from the beginning,

1113
01:08:26,670 --> 01:08:29,639
I don't want to spend
the rest of my life
in witness protection.

1114
01:08:29,773 --> 01:08:34,344
I'm not going to testify
against Mr. Saxon,
not now, not ever.

1115
01:08:34,478 --> 01:08:36,146
Excuse me.

1116
01:08:36,280 --> 01:08:38,815
JERRI: I never felt
that Barry
was rehabilitated.

1117
01:08:38,948 --> 01:08:42,352
FRANZESE: I believe
his transformation
was real.

1118
01:08:42,486 --> 01:08:47,257
MIKEY: Everyone in prison knew
that if you found Jesus

1119
01:08:47,391 --> 01:08:51,795
that would look good
on your record
to maybe get early release.

1120
01:08:51,928 --> 01:08:54,097
BARRY:
Truth plus time equal trust.

1121
01:08:54,231 --> 01:08:58,968
A lot of truth,
over a long period of time
equals trust.

1122
01:08:59,102 --> 01:09:01,738
And no shortcuts
to that equation either,
you know.

1123
01:09:05,275 --> 01:09:09,279
All right. We've heard
the testimony.

1124
01:09:09,413 --> 01:09:14,150
Now, it's time to decide
based on Mr. Minkow's
present character.

1125
01:09:27,497 --> 01:09:31,435
FRANZESE: You know, he came
out of prison raring to go.

1126
01:09:31,568 --> 01:09:35,205
But I didn't see it coming
with the church,
quite honestly.

1127
01:09:35,339 --> 01:09:40,577
Mr. Minkow, we have
gone through your application

1128
01:09:40,710 --> 01:09:43,046
and enjoyed your guest sermon,

1129
01:09:43,179 --> 01:09:48,685
but now we'd like
to hear the answer
to the following question.

1130
01:09:48,818 --> 01:09:50,554
Why should we hire you?

1131
01:09:53,823 --> 01:09:56,025
Well, on paper,
you shouldn't.

1132
01:09:56,159 --> 01:09:58,362
Especially when you
consider the fact that

1133
01:09:58,495 --> 01:10:01,865
the other 199 applicants
aren't convicted felons.

1134
01:10:06,970 --> 01:10:09,839
If you hire me,
I can promise you one thing,

1135
01:10:09,973 --> 01:10:12,576
that no one will work harder,
if for no other reason

1136
01:10:12,709 --> 01:10:16,480
than out of gratitude
for being given
the opportunity

1137
01:10:16,613 --> 01:10:18,815
to pastor such a great church.

1138
01:10:21,818 --> 01:10:24,454
You see, I'm naive enough
to believe that

1139
01:10:24,588 --> 01:10:28,057
if you want to find
the best employee,
the best place to find one

1140
01:10:28,191 --> 01:10:30,527
is someone who's
just come out of prison,

1141
01:10:30,660 --> 01:10:32,296
who didn't fail jail.

1142
01:10:33,497 --> 01:10:36,433
Who owes society
for what they've...

1143
01:10:38,502 --> 01:10:40,437
I've done.

1144
01:10:40,570 --> 01:10:46,410
And what better way
for a church to show their
belief in the gospel of grace

1145
01:10:46,543 --> 01:10:51,214
than have a broken vessel
like me proclaim that truth

1146
01:10:51,348 --> 01:10:53,583
from the pulpit
of this very church.

1147
01:10:53,717 --> 01:10:57,921
And from
a marketing standpoint,
imagine a slogan,

1148
01:10:58,054 --> 01:10:59,623
"Community Bible Church,

1149
01:10:59,756 --> 01:11:03,627
the only church
where the pastor
is far worse than you."

1150
01:11:07,464 --> 01:11:09,966
FRANZESE: I'll tell ya,
I don't know if you ever
saw him in church,

1151
01:11:10,099 --> 01:11:12,936
in front of his congregation,
he was masterful.

1152
01:11:13,069 --> 01:11:15,605
I mean, he had them
in the palm of his hands.

1153
01:11:15,739 --> 01:11:18,041
Thank you. Nice to meet you.

1154
01:11:20,744 --> 01:11:22,145
Hi.
Hi.

1155
01:11:22,278 --> 01:11:24,748
Nice to meet you.
Thank you for coming.

1156
01:11:24,881 --> 01:11:28,952
First time here?
Yes. Wonderful sermon,
Pastor Minkow.

1157
01:11:29,085 --> 01:11:31,721
Pastor Barry, please.
And this is my wife Lisa.

1158
01:11:31,855 --> 01:11:33,156
Hi, it's a pleasure
to meet you.

1159
01:11:33,289 --> 01:11:35,892
Hi, I'm Ellen Scott
and this is my husband Don.

1160
01:11:36,025 --> 01:11:37,527
Don, it's good to meet you.

1161
01:11:37,661 --> 01:11:39,863
We drove down
from Santa Barbara.
Santa Barbara?

1162
01:11:39,996 --> 01:11:43,132
Well, my sermons don't merit
that kind of sacrifice,
but thank you anyway.

1163
01:11:43,266 --> 01:11:46,135
We're here
for another reason.

1164
01:11:48,372 --> 01:11:53,877
The past 10 years, we put
all our retirement savings
in a hedge fund.

1165
01:11:54,010 --> 01:11:57,046
About $250,000.

1166
01:11:57,180 --> 01:12:00,550
I earned that money,
working 31 years
as a longshoreman.

1167
01:12:00,684 --> 01:12:07,156
Now we're worried about
the fund and thought you
could check it out.

1168
01:12:07,290 --> 01:12:08,892
Ma'am, I'm sorry,
I'm a pastor.

1169
01:12:09,025 --> 01:12:11,528
I don't really know
a whole lot
about hedge funds.

1170
01:12:11,661 --> 01:12:16,332
I'm really sorry. I...
Look, why are you concerned?

1171
01:12:16,466 --> 01:12:19,035
The manager
just moved his office
to the Bahamas.

1172
01:12:19,168 --> 01:12:20,870
How long
have they been around?

1173
01:12:21,004 --> 01:12:25,675
Twenty years. They're
worth around $800 million,
about 2,000 investors.

1174
01:12:25,809 --> 01:12:27,844
Twenty years, $800 million...

1175
01:12:27,977 --> 01:12:30,013
Sounds like you don't have
a whole lot to worry
about there.

1176
01:12:30,146 --> 01:12:34,851
Please, would you check on it?
I brought the prospectus.

1177
01:12:34,984 --> 01:12:37,320
Why me? I'm not an expert
in these kind of things.

1178
01:12:37,454 --> 01:12:41,525
Everything was fine
until I tried to withdraw
the money.

1179
01:12:41,658 --> 01:12:46,496
They've been telling me
that it's in process
for three months.

1180
01:12:46,630 --> 01:12:51,334
I told my nephew about it
and he suggested I see you.

1181
01:12:51,468 --> 01:12:55,338
Your nephew.
Who's your nephew?

1182
01:13:01,911 --> 01:13:03,079
Mike?

1183
01:13:03,980 --> 01:13:07,050
Mike

1184
01:13:08,852 --> 01:13:11,555
You look great.
You look great.

1185
01:13:11,688 --> 01:13:13,590
Not even you can
pull off that lie.

1186
01:13:13,723 --> 01:13:17,393
Well, I'm not exactly
winning any beauty
contests myself.

1187
01:13:17,527 --> 01:13:19,095
How you been?

1188
01:13:19,228 --> 01:13:21,831
I'll be a lot better
if you tell me you can
help out my uncle.

1189
01:13:21,965 --> 01:13:23,366
Yeah, well...

1190
01:13:23,500 --> 01:13:27,203
This hedge-fund guy, Lewis,
right, he's telling me

1191
01:13:27,336 --> 01:13:30,674
he's getting monthly gains
of 1.5% to 3.5%.

1192
01:13:30,807 --> 01:13:34,711
Yeah, I don't think anybody's
quite that good.

1193
01:13:34,844 --> 01:13:36,212
Hedge fund, I...

1194
01:13:36,345 --> 01:13:37,981
You know, I got that letter
you wrote to me from prison,

1195
01:13:38,114 --> 01:13:39,949
apologizing for what you did.

1196
01:13:40,083 --> 01:13:43,319
Were you lying then
or are you lying now?

1197
01:13:43,453 --> 01:13:47,390
Look, Mike, I'm not
the same guy I was before.

1198
01:13:47,524 --> 01:13:50,794
I'm married.
I got the church.
I got twins.

1199
01:13:50,927 --> 01:13:53,830
I teach the FBI
in fraud prevention
in Quantico. I...

1200
01:13:53,963 --> 01:13:57,567
I don't really want to hear
about the good deeds
of my old schoolmates.

1201
01:13:57,701 --> 01:13:59,603
You can tell me you're working
with lepers on an island,

1202
01:13:59,736 --> 01:14:03,072
my opinion of you
wouldn't change, Barry. Okay?

1203
01:14:03,206 --> 01:14:06,042
I'll believe the change
when I see it.

1204
01:14:06,175 --> 01:14:09,713
Anybody who's ever been
in a financial dealing with me
has lived to regret it.

1205
01:14:09,846 --> 01:14:11,280
You know that.

1206
01:14:11,414 --> 01:14:14,050
Yeah, I'll take my chances.

1207
01:14:14,183 --> 01:14:16,986
Besides, your rates
are unbeatable.

1208
01:14:19,022 --> 01:14:22,391
Rates?
I don't have any rates.

1209
01:14:22,526 --> 01:14:23,627
Exactly.

1210
01:14:26,663 --> 01:14:30,834
MIKEY: It became just too much
of a temptation for him.

1211
01:14:30,967 --> 01:14:34,103
JERRI: Barry wanted
to kind of do
the Catch Me If You Can.

1212
01:14:34,237 --> 01:14:37,641
DAN: It was impressive.
I mean, he really
knew his stuff.

1213
01:14:37,774 --> 01:14:39,543
And there you have
the six red flags for fraud.

1214
01:14:39,676 --> 01:14:42,178
Should you choose to
commit those to memory,

1215
01:14:42,311 --> 01:14:43,713
you will be able to stop
the next Barry Minkow

1216
01:14:43,847 --> 01:14:45,749
before he is the next
Barry Minkow.

1217
01:14:45,882 --> 01:14:47,717
That's all I have today.
Thanks for joining me.

1218
